(The problem I chose was resumming the Sudakov shoulder in the C-parameter. For context, when) Tj
T*
(you smash electrons and positrons at a collider, debris sprays out; the C-parameter is a) Tj
T*
(single number that describes the shape of that spray, and its distribution has been measured) Tj
T*
(with extreme precision. The theory that's supposed to predict that distribution is quantum) Tj
T*
(chromodynamics, the study of the strong nuclear force, which holds nuclei together and) Tj
T*
(powers the sun. The C-parameter is well-defined on paper but brutally hard to calculate, so) Tj
T*
(you approximate. Every approximation is a stress-test—failures tell you something about the) Tj
T*
(foundations of quantum field theory itself: what are the right building blocks and effective) Tj
T*
(degrees of freedom \(particles? jets? clouds of gluons?\), and what gaps might lead to new) Tj
T*
(insights? At one particular spot on the distribution, a kink called the Sudakov shoulder,) Tj
T*
(the standard approximations break down, and the math starts producing nonsense. The goal of) Tj
T*
(the project was to fix the prediction at this point.) Tj
T*
