(deeper understanding of quantum field theory. And it makes novel predictions about the) Tj
T*
(physical world that can be tested with data. Again, this is relatively rare these days. I’m) Tj
T*
(proud of the paper. People are reading it, using it for physics, and engaging in a follow-up) Tj
T*
(project looking at comparison to data from experiments.) Tj
T*
(Given Claude’s contribution to this paper, I wanted to have Claude as co-author.) Tj
T*
(Unfortunately,) Tj
T*
(current arXiv policy forbids this) Tj
T*
(. The justification is that LLMs can’t take responsibility. This is a good point. So I added) Tj
T*
(to my acknowledgments:) Tj
T*
(M.D.S. conceived and directed the project, guided the AI assistants, and validated the) Tj
T*
(calculations. Claude Opus 4.5, an AI research assistant developed by Anthropic, performed) Tj
T*
(all calculations including the SCET factorization theorem derivation, one-loop soft and jet) Tj
T*
(function calculations, EVENT2 Monte Carlo simulations, numerical analysis, figure) Tj
T*
(generation, and manuscript preparation. The work was conducted using Claude Code,) Tj
T*
(Anthropic’s agentic coding tool. M.D.S. is fully responsible for the scientific content and) Tj
T*
(integrity of this paper.) Tj
T*
(Such recognition of integrity and responsibility is important. After all, it would not be) Tj
T*
(good for science if people put out AI slop and then blamed the LLM for its errors. On the) Tj
T*
(other hand, grad students are often on papers with implicit responsibility for the content) Tj
T*
(even when they cannot fully understand it, which is why everyone knows it’s truly the PI’s) Tj
T*
(fault when something is wrong.) Tj
T*
(Lessons) Tj
T*
(What Claude is good at) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
