stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
14 TL
54 738 Td
(around August 2025, when GPT-5 could do the coursework for basically any course we offer at) Tj
T*
(Harvard. By December 2025, Claude Opus 4.5 was at the G2 level.) Tj
T*
(What this means is that although LLMs cannot yet do original theoretical physics research) Tj
T*
(autonomously, they can vastly accelerate the research done by experts. For this project) Tj
T*
(\(which I completed with Claude in two weeks\), I’d estimate that it would have taken me and a) Tj
T*
(G2 student 1-2 years, and me without AI around 3-5 months. Ultimately, it accelerated my own) Tj
T*
(research tenfold. That’s game-changing!) Tj
T*
(There are two natural follow-up questions that arise from this project. How do we get from) Tj
T*
(here to an AI Ph.D.? And what are human grad students supposed to do now?) Tj
T*
(I don’t have great answers to these questions. By blunt extrapolation, LLMs will be at the) Tj
T*
(Ph.D or postdoc level in around a year \(March 2027\). I’m not sure how we’ll get there—maybe) Tj
T*
(we need domain experts to train them, maybe they will train themselves, maybe it will be) Tj
T*
(some combination of the two. I am more confident that the bottleneck is not creativity. LLMs) Tj
T*
(are profoundly creative. They simply lack a sense of which paths might be fruitful before) Tj
T*
(walking them. I think we can distill what is missing in current LLMs to a single word:) Tj
T*
(Taste) Tj
T*
(.) Tj
T*
(In physics, taste is the intangible sense about which research directions might lead) Tj
T*
(somewhere. I've been doing research in theoretical physics for a long time and have learned) Tj
T*
(to tell pretty quickly whether an idea is promising or not. I suspect anyone who has honed a) Tj
T*
(craft for a long time—whether in science, carpentry, or design—would recognize this:) Tj
T*
(experience produces a kind of judgment that AI has not yet mastered. We do not give enough) Tj
T*
(credit to taste. When solving problems is hard, the solution gets the glory, but when) Tj
T*
(knowledge and technical strength are ubiquitous, it’s the taste to come up with good ideas) Tj
T*
(that distinguishes great work.) Tj
T*
(Regarding the question of where this leaves human grad students, my advice to students at) Tj
T*
(all levels \(and in any field\) is to take LLMs seriously. Do not fall into the hallucination) Tj
T*
(trap: “I asked the LLM X and it made something up, so I’m just going to wait for it to) Tj
T*
(improve.” Instead, get to know these models. Learn what they are good at and what they fail) Tj
T*
(at. Buy the $20 subscription. It will change your life.) Tj
T*
(For students interested in scientific careers, I would advise looking into experimental) Tj
T*
(science—particularly fields that require hands-on empirical work and involve problems that) Tj
T*
(cannot be solved by pure thought alone. No amount of compute can tell Claude what is) Tj
T*
(actually in a human cell, or if the San Andreas fault is growing with time. You need) Tj
T*
(measurements. Much experimental work will still have to be done by human scientists.) Tj
T*
(Remember, a vast amount of experimental physics doesn’t look like sleek, automated data) Tj
T*
(collection; it looks like blindly reaching into a cramped vacuum chamber to tighten a) Tj
T*
(stubborn steel flange by feel, or tweaking the micrometer knobs on an optical table to align) Tj
T*
(a laser beam by a fraction of a millimeter. Engineering a robotic hand with the tactile) Tj
T*
(feedback necessary to safely and gently replicate that kind of messy, everyday dexterity is) Tj
T*
(staggeringly difficult and expensive. Just as search-and-rescue teams still deploy trained) Tj
T*
(dogs to navigate dense, collapsed rubble, I’m sure experimental science will rely on human) Tj
T*
(labor for the foreseeable future \(although AI will certainly be) Tj
T*
(bossing us around) Tj
T*
(!\).) Tj
T*
(It is worth it, however, to consider the role of education going forward. In the deep future) Tj
T*
(\(~10 years\), when AI is truly smarter than all of us and capable of outperforming us in) Tj
T*
(every domain, what will be the role of higher education? I think some things will) Tj
ET
endstream
